(42, 19, 7, 42, 5, 30, 30, 'murmured', 'Murmuring About Sinners', 'Both passages emphasize the murmuring of the crowd regarding Jesus associating with sinners. This connection highlights the criticism faced by Jesus for his choice of company.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 7, 42, 18, 9, 14, 'man that is a sinner', 'Theme of Sinners and Righteousness', 'Both passages emphasize the contrast between sinners and the self-righteous. In Luke 19:7, the murmuring about Jesus dining with a ''sinner'' parallels the Pharisee''s disdain for the publican in Luke 18:9-14.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 7, 40, 21, 28, 31, 'man that is a sinner', 'Connection of Sinners and Repentance', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of sinners responding to God''s call. In Luke, the murmuring about Jesus dining with a ''sinner'' reflects societal judgment, while in Matthew, the first son represents those who initially reject but later repent, illustrating a similar dynamic of acceptance and transformation.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 8, 10, 12, 6, 6, 'restore him fourfold', 'Restoration and Repentance Theme', 'Both passages emphasize the act of restoration, with Zaccheus promising to restore fourfold what he wrongfully took, paralleling the judgment in 2 Samuel where restoration is mandated. This connection highlights the moral imperative of making amends for wrongdoing.', 'theme', 0.45399999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 8, 4, 5, 7, 7, 'restore him fourfold', 'Restitution and Confession', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of restitution for wrongs done. Zaccheus pledges to restore what he has taken, paralleling the requirement in Numbers to recompense with additional restitution.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 8, 42, 18, 22, 23, NULL, 'Wealth and Generosity Connection', 'Both passages emphasize the theme of wealth and its relationship to generosity. Zaccheus''s commitment to give to the poor parallels Jesus''s instruction to the rich ruler to sell all he has and distribute to the poor.', 'theme', 0.37, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 8, 3, 6, 1, 6, 'restore him fourfold', 'Restitution and Repentance', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of restoring what was wrongfully taken. Zaccheus'' commitment to restore fourfold aligns with the principle of restitution outlined in Leviticus.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 8, 20, 6, 31, 31, 'restore him fourfold', 'Restitution and Generosity Theme', 'This connection highlights the theme of restitution for wrongs done. Both passages emphasize the importance of restoring what was taken, with Zaccheus committing to restore fourfold, while Proverbs states a sevenfold restoration.', 'theme', 0.356, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 8, 2, 22, 1, 4, 'restore him fourfold', 'Restitution and Generosity', 'This connection highlights the theme of restitution found in both passages. Zaccheus''s commitment to restore fourfold for any wrongs parallels the restitution principles outlined in Exodus.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 8, 42, 12, 33, 33, NULL, 'Connection of Generosity and Almsgiving', 'Both passages emphasize the importance of giving to the poor and restoring what is wrongfully taken. Zaccheus''s commitment to give alms and restore fourfold aligns with the call to sell possessions and provide for others in Luke 12:33.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 9, 48, 3, 7, 7, 'son of Abraham', 'Children of Abraham Connection', 'This connection highlights the theme of faith as the basis for being considered a child of Abraham. In both passages, the identity of being a ''son of Abraham'' is linked to faith, emphasizing that salvation and belonging to God''s family are accessible through belief.', 'theme', 0.46099999999999997, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 9, 42, 13, 16, 16, 'son of Abraham', 'Connection of Abraham''s Children', 'Both passages emphasize the identity of individuals as ''sons'' or ''daughters of Abraham,'' highlighting their inclusion in God''s covenant. This connection underscores the theme of salvation and healing extended to those considered part of Abraham''s lineage.', 'theme', 0.419, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 9, 45, 4, 16, 16, 'son of Abraham', 'Connection of Faith and Salvation', 'This connection highlights the theme of faith leading to salvation. Both passages emphasize the significance of being a ''son of Abraham'' through faith, linking the promise of salvation to all who believe.', 'theme', 0.412, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 9, 44, 16, 30, 32, 'salvation come to this house', 'Salvation for Households', 'This connection highlights the theme of salvation extending to households. Both passages emphasize that salvation is not only for individuals but also encompasses their families.', 'theme', 0.398, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 9, 48, 3, 29, 29, 'son of Abraham', 'Connection of Abraham''s Seed', 'This connection highlights the concept of being a ''son of Abraham'' and ''Abraham''s seed.'' Both passages emphasize the inclusion of believers in the promise of salvation and inheritance through faith.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 9, 60, 2, 10, 10, 'salvation come to this house', 'Salvation and People of God', 'This connection highlights the theme of salvation and belonging to Godâ€™s people. Both passages emphasize the transition from exclusion to inclusion, with Luke 19:9 stating that salvation has come, while 1 Peter 2:10 speaks of becoming the people of God.', 'theme', 0.384, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 9, 42, 3, 8, 8, 'son of Abraham', 'Connection of Abraham''s Children', 'Both passages emphasize the significance of being a ''son of Abraham.'' In Luke 19:9, Jesus acknowledges Zacchaeus as a son of Abraham, while Luke 3:8 warns against relying solely on Abrahamic lineage for salvation.', 'theme', 0.377, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 10, 26, 34, 16, 16, NULL, 'Seeking the Lost', 'Both passages emphasize the act of seeking what is lost. Luke 19:10 states the purpose of the Son of Man is to seek and save the lost, while Ezekiel 34:16 expresses God''s intention to seek that which was lost.', 'theme', 1.0, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 10, 40, 1, 21, 21, 'save that which was lost', 'Connection of Salvation Purpose', 'Both passages emphasize the purpose of Jesus'' mission to save. Luke 19:10 states He came to ''save that which was lost,'' while Matthew 1:21 specifies He will ''save his people from their sins.''', 'theme', 0.937, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 10, 54, 1, 13, 16, 'to seek and to save that which was lost', 'Salvation of the Lost', 'Both passages emphasize the mission of Christ to save those who are lost or sinners. Luke 19:10 states that Jesus came to seek and save the lost, while 1 Timothy 1:15 affirms that Christ Jesus came into the world to save sinners, highlighting the theme of mercy and redemption.', 'theme', 0.867, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 10, 42, 5, 31, 32, 'to seek and to save', 'Mission of Jesus', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' mission to reach those in need. Luke 19:10 highlights His purpose to save the lost, while Luke 5:31-32 specifies that He calls sinners to repentance.', 'theme', 0.853, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 10, 42, 15, 4, 7, 'to seek and to save that which was lost', 'Connection of Seeking the Lost', 'This connection highlights the theme of seeking and saving the lost. Both passages emphasize the importance of finding what is lost, with the shepherd leaving the ninety-nine sheep to seek the one that is lost, paralleling the mission of the Son of man.', 'theme', 0.7829999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 10, 40, 9, 12, 13, 'to seek and to save', 'Connection of Seeking and Saving', 'Both passages emphasize Jesus'' mission to reach those who are lost or in need of healing. Luke 19:10 speaks of seeking and saving the lost, while Matthew 9:12-13 highlights calling sinners to repentance, indicating a focus on the marginalized.', 'theme', 0.7689999999999999, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 10, 45, 5, 6, 6, 'to seek and to save', 'Connection of Salvation Themes', 'Both passages emphasize Christ''s mission to save those who are lost or ungodly. Luke 19:10 highlights the seeking nature of Christ, while Romans 5:6 underscores His sacrificial death for the ungodly.', 'theme', 0.734, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 11, 42, 17, 20, 20, 'the kingdom of God should immediately appear', 'Expectation of the Kingdom', 'Both passages emphasize the nature of the kingdom of God and the misunderstanding surrounding its arrival. In Luke 19:11, the expectation is that the kingdom should appear immediately, while Luke 17:20 clarifies that it does not come with observation.', 'theme', 0.349, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 11, 44, 1, 6, 6, 'the kingdom of God should immediately appear', 'Expectation of God''s Kingdom', 'Both passages emphasize the anticipation of the kingdom of God. In Luke, the people expect its immediate appearance, while in Acts, the disciples inquire about its restoration to Israel.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 11, 53, 2, 1, 3, 'the kingdom of God should immediately appear', 'Expectation of the Kingdom', 'Both passages emphasize the anticipation of the coming of the Lord and the establishment of God''s kingdom. Luke highlights the expectation of the kingdom''s immediate appearance, while 2 Thessalonians addresses concerns about the timing of Christ''s return.', 'theme', 0.314, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 12, 40, 25, 14, 30, 'a certain nobleman went into a far country', 'Nobleman and Servants Connection', 'Both passages emphasize a nobleman or lord who goes into a far country, highlighting themes of stewardship and accountability. The expectation of the servants to manage resources during the nobleman''s absence connects the two narratives.', 'theme', 0.391, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 12, 42, 19, 12, 27, 'A certain nobleman went into a far country to receive for himself a kingdom, and to return.', 'Nobleman and Servants Connection', 'This connection highlights the nobleman''s journey to receive a kingdom and his subsequent interactions with his servants. Both passages emphasize the themes of authority, responsibility, and the consequences of actions taken during the nobleman''s absence.', 'theme', 0.33499999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini'),
(42, 19, 12, 42, 20, 9, 9, 'went into a far country', 'Journey to a Far Country', 'Both passages emphasize a departure to a far country, suggesting a theme of absence and expectation. The nobleman and the man with the vineyard both leave their responsibilities for an extended period.', 'theme', 0.32799999999999996, 'high', 'v1.2', 'gpt-4o-mini')
